comments.content:
Allright, i think i have A solution. For me, this works:

On the controller node in the /etc/nova/nova.conf file I used the deprecated "admin" variables.

So under the [neutron] head there are the following variables:

[neutron]
url = http://x.x.x.x:9696
auth_strategy = keystone
admin_auth_url = http://x.x.x.x:35357
admin_tenant_name = service
admin_username = neutron
admin_password = password
service_metadata_proxy = True
metadata_proxy_shared_secret = secret

NOW comment out the admin variables and add the auth_plugin with the authentication variables:

url = http://x.x.x.x:9696
auth_strategy = keystone
##admin_auth_url = http://x.x.x.x:35357
##admin_tenant_name = service
##admin_username = neutron
##admin_password = password
auth_url = http://x.x.x.x:35357
auth_plugin = password
project_domain_id = default
user_domain_id = default
region_name = RegionOne
project_name = service
username = neutron
password = password
service_metadata_proxy = True
metadata_proxy_shared_secret = secret

Again, this works for me. Please let me know if this is the solution for you to Arun V.
comments.author: https://api.launchpad.net/1.0/~gtman558
